                            <comment id="13190674" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 22 Jan 2012 13:25:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have to agree with Peter. To cache a font one has to ensure that fonts are 100% equal, which is possible but complicated. It&apos;s not enough to just compare the name, the subtype and the encoding. I stumbled upon this issue when rendering the Centerplan.pdf attached to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-615&quot; title=&quot;shfill operator needs implementation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-615&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-615&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I removed the font caching in revision 1234506. I improved and hopefully simplified the handling of resources of a pdf as well. On one hand these changes may have an negative impact on the performance because of the missing font cache, but on the other hand all fonts are handled correct now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
